requirements-dev: remove tox (#71)

Tox config has been removed in 09bab2e, and while it might be worth
bringing it back, there is no point in installing tox in a virtualenv
(`python -m venv .venv`) to run the tests without tox therein.
Release 0.14.0

Remove trailing dot from checker messages (#70)

Hi there,

Your checker is a work of genius! However, it would be nice to remove trailing dots from the checker messages, such that they don't stand out as compared to all other flake8 checks.

Many thanks!
Release 0.13.1
Added a note about escaping quotes in the doc (#68)
Release 0.13.0

Moved to twine for upload (#62)

PyPI has dropped support for uploading via `setup.py upload` due to security concerns. The recommended alternative is to use `twine`:

https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/distributing-packages/#uploading-your-project-to-pypi

In this PR:

- Updated `release.sh` to use `twine`

commit.message:
Run Travis tests on Python 3.4-3.6 (#63)

* Run Travis tests on Python 3.4-3.6

* Update PyPI classifiers to note Python 3.3, 3.5, 3.6 support

* Remove special case installing flake8 3

`requirements-dev.txt` is now specifies flake8 3 anyway, so this special case does not affect the CI build.

* Drop Python 3.3 from Travis build

* Remove Python 3.3 from PyPI classifier
